  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through complex transactions or legitimate businesses. Typically, it involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's origin\n3. Integration - withdrawing the now \"cleaned\" money and using it seemingly legitimately\n\nThe specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most countries criminalize these activities under anti-money laundering (AML) laws.",
